27 additional credit equal to 5 percent of qualified rehabilitation expenditures shall be
28 allowed; and
29 (2)(B) In the case of any other certified structure, equal to 25 20 percent of qualified
30 rehabilitation expenditures.
31 (2) Qualified rehabilitation expenditures may only be counted once in determining the
32 amount of the tax credit available, and more than one entity may shall not claim a credit
33 for the same qualified rehabilitation expenditures.
34 (c)(1) In no event shall credits for a historic home exceed $100,000.00 in any 120 month
35 period.
36 (2) The maximum credit for any other individual certified structure shall be $5 million
37 for any taxable year, except in the case that the project creates 200 or more full-time,
38 permanent jobs or $5 million in annual payroll within two years of the placed in service
39 date, in which case the project is eligible for credits up to $10 million for an individual
40 certified structure. In no event shall more than one application for any individual
41 certified structure under this paragraph be approved in any 120 month period.
42 (3)(A) In no event shall credits issued under this Code section for historic homes
43 exceed $5 million in aggregate per year.
